Rating: 4
I've made this chili, and several variations of it after experimenting, many times. It's the best chili I've had. This chili does improve from the addition of 1/2 a cinnamon stick and 1 tsp cumin, though. Just add the cinnamon when you add the liquids and fish it out after about 30-40 minutes of cooking. Other variations - ground turkey instead of beef; addition of vegetables such as finely diced carrots, bell peppers and zucchini with the onions; pinto beans in place of some or all of the black beans. I've also found that if you want to cut the time down on cooking and you're using a lean meat, it's not necessary to sauté the meat and vegetables seperately. If your chili turns out a bit thin and/or you don't have cornmeal, tomato paste helps thicken it.

