Rating: 3
A very good, quick chili. To sum up my observations and others: (1) play around with the meat/bean combo. I used 1/2 beef, 1/2 pork, others use kidney, pink, whatever beans--do what you like. (2) Fresh cilantro on top--who doesn't like that? (3) Try a Mexican Creme Fresca (sp?) if you can find it--it's the texture of sour cream blended with yogurt but it has the tangy bite of sour cream, if not more. Very good addition. (4) Instead of adjusting the chili powder amounts, adjust the amount of chipotle in adobo. I usually process a can and then use it by the tablespoon GRADUALLY to add just the right amount of heat and smoky flavor. It can be added late, instead of chili powder which needs to cook to develop flavor. Or, scoop out a cup of chili, make it ridiculously hot and let your guests add tablespoons to their liking.

