Delicious. I'm from chili country and this is a great variation. Had no "stout" so I used non-alcoholic beer which worked fine. Also added some concentrated beef juice from roast. Great depth of flavor. Try it with low fat (not nonfat) sour cream. I cut the amount of chili powder by half...personal preference. Still plenty spicy.

Rating: 2
I made a completely VEGAN version of this recipe by substituting the ground beef with one package of Boca ground beef substitute, one can of red kidney beans, and half a bag of frozen corn (it was already opened and just taking up space so i figured "what the hell"). Obviously sub'd beef broth with veggie. I used a sour cream substitute which at first seemed really stiff and un-sour cream like, but the texture loosened up with the addition of the lime juice. The wannabe gourmet grocery story that I went to didn't have canned chipotles, so I used some ancho chili paste. Overall, it's pretty good, it has an interesting flavor. It's a good jumping off point for a chili recipe, start with this and make your own additions and stuff. **Needs lots of cayenne for some kick**

