Rating: 3
I like my chili spicy and tomato-y so I made a couple of changes. Specifically, I added a 6-oz. can of tomato paste, substituted the crushed tomatoes w/ 1 can of drained, mashed Ro-Tel tomatoes, substituted 1 can of Campbell's beef consomme' & 1 can water for the broth, upped the stout to 1 12-oz. bottle of Guinness, and doubled the amount of chipotles (canned with adobo sauce). I'm serving this tonight for the Superbowl so I'll have to wait to get my guests' reactions, but for my taste this recipe is excellent!

